        "title": "Repair invoke-style plain-text tool calls",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Extend plain-text tool-call repair to recognize XML-ish `<invoke name=\"...\">` calls with named `<parameter name=\"...\">` arguments.\n- Keep streamed invoke-style tool-call text buffered so it can be promoted into structured tool-call events instead of leaking as assistant text.\n- Allow standalone text tool-call promotion when the terminal reason is `toolUse`, improving compatibility with models such as Opus 4.8 that may emit XML-ish tool-call text.\n\n## Behavior\nThis only affects malformed/plain-text tool-call repair paths. Normal structured tool calls continue to use the existing provider-native flow unchanged.\n\n## Testing\n- `corepack pnpm exec tsx -` smoke test for `parseStandalonePlainTextToolCallBlocks` with `call\\n<invoke name=\"exec\">...`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.unit-fast.config.ts src/shared/text/tool-call-shaped-text.test.ts --reporter=dot --maxWorkers=1`\r\n",
